This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dale Alfonze Johnson not in court, in custody.  Attorney Fred Richardson III in court for Dale Alfonze Johnson. Assistant District Attorney Alicia H Kort in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant's appearance waived.  Defense is requesting court dates for final pretrial and jury trial.  Court advised parties all pre trial documents are to be filed 48 hours in advance of pre trial.  If motions are to be filed the deadline for filing is 10/28, any reply/response is due by 11/30/22. Parties to contact the clerk for motion hearing date.   mn

Defendant Dale Alfonze Johnson not in court, in custody.  Attorney Fred Richardson III in court for Dale Alfonze Johnson.  Attorney Erin Karshen appeared on behalf  of Attorney Alicia H Kort for the State of Wisconsin. 

Case in Court for Scheduling Conference. Discussion placed on the record. Defense received discovery material from the State. Defense requested a date for a Scheduling hearing to allow time to review Discovery. State did not object. Case adjourned for Scheduling hearing. Case remains calendared in Branch 45. 

Scheduling hearing scheduled for September 30, 2022 at 9:45 am. Hearing will be held in Room G55 of the Criminal Justice Facility.

Defendant Dale Alfonze Johnson appeared by video, in custody in HOC.  Attorney Fred Richardson III in court in person for Dale Alfonze Johnson.  Prosecuting attorney Abby Rockendorf in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer A. Navone. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 45.
Scheduling conference scheduled for September 6, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Fred Richardson in court, defendant Dale Alfonze Johnson not in court, in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness is present. Defendant is in a COVID pod and not available by video in a timely manner. Due to the lateness of the hour Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 31, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Dale Alfonze Johnson not in court, defendant in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for preliminary hearing. States witness is not present. OPD needs additional time to appoint an attorney. State requests that this matter be set in the trial court for a State V. Lee hearing; denied. Court finds good CAUSE to adjourn preliminary hearing.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 26, 2022 at 08:30 am.
No Contact Order signed and filed.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for Level 5 Supervision with Electronic Monitoring.  24 hour curfew. If electronic monitoring device is unavailable and cash bail has been paid, bail to revert to $35,000.00.  If Alternative bail is paid, Defendant to be released and placed on Electronic Monitoring waiting list.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with LEH (DOB 01/05/2005), her immediate family, or her residence.  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Dale Alfonze Johnson in court with attorney Fred Richardson.  Defendant Dale Alfonze Johnson in custody. Adam Best appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Dale Alfonze Johnson appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Yamahiro, Branch 34.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised if DNA sample has NOT been obtained from the Defendant Court orders the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to obtain DNA sample from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4)  All parties are notified that effective July 30, 2022, this case will be assigned to Judge Jean Kies, Br 45, room 502 SB  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 29, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
